{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Take advantage of custom decoding and encoding logic for the shared file storage persistence","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"strategy, as well as beta support for Swift’s native Testing framework.","type":"text"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.19","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.18","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.15","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.14","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.13","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.11","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.10","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.9","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.8","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.7","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.6","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.5","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.4"]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.12"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.12"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library introduced 1 new","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"API, as well as beta support for Swift Testing.","type":"text"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tools of version 1.11. See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for more information."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"important","type":"aside","name":"Important"},{"anchor":"Custom-file-storage-coding","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Custom file storage coding"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Version 1.10 of the Composable Architecture introduced a powerful tool for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"sharing state","type":"reference","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"sharing state"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState"},{"type":"text","text":" amongst your features, and included several built-in persistence"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"strategies, including file storage. This strategy, however, was not very flexible, and only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"supported the default JSON encoding and decoding offered by Swift."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In this version, you can now define custom encoding and decoding logic using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage(_:decode:encode:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"anchor":"Swift-Testing","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Swift Testing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Xcode 16 and Swift 6 come with a powerful new native testing framework. Existing test targets using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"XCTest can even incrementally adopt the framework and define new tests with Testing. Existing XCTest","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"test ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"helpers","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", however, are not compatible with the new framework, and so test tools like the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Composable Architecture’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TestStore"},{"text":" did not work with it out of the box.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That changes with this version, which seamlessly supports XCTest "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"and"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Swift’s Testing framework."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can now create a test store in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Test"},{"type":"text","text":" and failures will be reported accordingly."}]}]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"title":"Migrating to 1.12"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"kind":"article","references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/MigratingTo1.17":{"type":"topic","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Migra